  <h1>Web Development Curriculum</h1>

  <p><strong>Course Title:</strong> <em>Introduction to Web Development</em></p>
  <p><u>Semester:</u> First Year, Semester 2</p>
  <p>This course introduces students to the fundamentals of web technologies, including HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It emphasizes hands-on learning and project-based development.</p>

  <h2>Course Objectives</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Understand the structure and syntax of HTML.</li>
    <li>Apply CSS for styling web pages.</li>
    <li>Use JavaScript for interactivity.</li>
    <li>Develop responsive and accessible websites.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Course Modules</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>HTML Basics</li>
    <li>CSS Styling</li>
    <li>JavaScript Fundamentals</li>
    <li>Responsive Design</li>
    <li>Project Work</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Module Details</h2>
  <dl>
    <dt><strong>HTML Basics</strong></dt>
    <dd>Introduction to tags, elements, attributes, and page structure.</dd>

    <dt><strong>CSS Styling</strong></dt>
    <dd>Selectors, properties, box model, and layout techniques.</dd>

    <dt><strong>JavaScript Fundamentals</strong></dt>
    <dd>Variables, functions, events, and DOM manipulation.</dd>
  </dl>

  <h2>Assessment Criteria</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Assignments</strong>
      <ol>
        <li>HTML Page Creation</li>
        <li>CSS Styling Challenge</li>
        <li>JavaScript Mini Project</li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Mid-Term Exam</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Final Project</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Team-based website development</li>
        <li>Presentation & Documentation</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Special Notes</h2>
  <p>Make sure to use semantic tags and follow <strong>W3C standards</strong>. Pay attention to accessibility and cross-browser compatibility.</p>
  <p>Special characters to know: &lt;, &gt;, &amp;, &copy;, &reg;</p>

</body>
</html>